$ Shell command: loadkeys
@ loadkeys

code {
$ loadkeys de-latin1
code }

code {
$ loadkeys de
code }

`loadkeys` loads the kernel keymap (keyboard translation table) for the console.

`loadkeys` can be run by everyone with access to → Linux/fhs/dev/console.

The keyboard translation table is shared by all virtual consoles. So, loading a new translation table affects all users connected via virtual consoles.



{ --mktable

  → Linux/kernel/source/drivers/tty/vt/defkeymap_c

}

